  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;Title&gt;Brilliant! Brilliant!&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Peter Hewitt&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;Reception: Very friendly and professional, I was able to have a little light banter, which helped putting me at ease.
The first nurse: Again very professional and friendly. She first checked all my details drew a nice arrow above the eye that I was being operated on. Then she applied various drops to my eye. She then took me into the next room, where she told me where the toilets were, and where to get a drink. 
Operating Staff: two again very friendly and professional ladies took me into another room where they put some more drops into my eye, and explained everything in detail that would happen in the operating theatre.
Surgeon: He again was very friendly and professional, He came into the waiting room and explained what would happen during the operation.
Operating theatre: All through the operation the surgeon explained what he was doing, all the time talking very calmly, which helped to put me at ease. Apart from a little discomfort when putting on the face covering to hold open my eye the operation was totally painless. I am not sure how long the operation took but it only felt like about 10 minutes. After the operation the staff applied some covering to my eye and gave me some instructions on how to take care of my eye.
Post operation:  I then went into another room where a lady, who again was very friendly and professional, gave me a bag with eye drops and various items and instructions on how to take care of my eye.
Finish: I signed through reception, and went home. The whole experience lasted about 2 hours.
Result: The rest of the day my eye felt uncomfortable. The day after, I can only say the world opened up to me, colours seemed to leap out of everything I looked at. I was overwhelmed, I felt like laughing and crying at the same time. I had not realised how bad my eyesight had become. 
All I can say is thankyou to everyone involved in my care at the SpaMedica Hull. You are all fantastic. You have changed my life so much for the better.       
&lt;/CommentText&gt;
